Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.14,0:00:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is indeed the time to start Kaleido Star.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.08,0:00:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When you watch Kaleido Star, I think \Nyou should keep your room brightly lit{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.08,0:00:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and sit as far from the TV as you can.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.04,0:00:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, well, well. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Have you ever had something \Nimportant to you end?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.46,0:00:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we had fun, when we had tough times,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.59,0:00:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}when we laughed and cried, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.10,0:00:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the precious memories \Nthat we made together...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.30,0:00:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Being thankful for many, many things.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But, we can't let it end like this. Don't \Nyou think? Don't you think? Don't you think?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The dream everyone is looking \Nfor must be someplace{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.02,0:00:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It has to be somewhere {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:01:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until your dream comes true \Nsomeday, you're not alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.25,0:01:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Remember how I used to say \NI could make it to the end?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I must have been pretending to be tough{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything I did was reckless \Nand it never got me anywhere{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.56,0:01:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But you alone were always beside me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.95,0:01:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The dream everyone is looking \Nfor must be somewhere{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.91,0:01:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You can start going forward {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From this moment, something will start{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.13,0:01:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe that {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.17,0:02:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The light I haven't seen yet is \Nbeaming toward the promised place{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.68,0:02:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until your dream comes true \Nsomeday, you're not alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora! It was the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.60,0:02:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two weeks from opening day,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.50,0:02:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the audience's reaction started changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.58,0:02:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you read today's newspaper?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.71,0:02:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaleido Stage's new director, Mia Guillem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.31,0:02:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her appearance has been more \Ndramatic than Halley's Comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, of course, I deserve \Nto get that comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think you'll get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.07,0:03:02.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Yuri's Amazing Trap."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.66,0:03:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was concern that Kaleido Stage \Nwould grow smaller and weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is plenty of possibility \Nthat it will regain its strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.33,0:03:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.54,0:03:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means that no matter how \NYuri tries to obstruct us,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,people cannot ignore a really nice show.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.34,0:03:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen all kinds of shows,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.30,0:03:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but, even setting aside favoritism, \NI think this show is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.35,0:03:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.13,0:03:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad is an old-fashioned type kind of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.10,0:03:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he can't tell a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Marion...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it would be nice if this show kept \Non like this and became a long run.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.40,0:03:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.49,0:03:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if the audience keeps \Ngrowing like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we'll even get lots \Nof sponsors signing on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.20,0:03:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you should \Nget overexcited about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.16,0:03:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, you missed the timing \Nat the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.67,0:03:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia, your face is too tense sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.17,0:04:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora, you let yourself go, \Nand make your moves too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.23,0:04:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep doing that, the lighting \Ntechnician cannot keep up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.55,0:04:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot call our performance \Nperfect by any means.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.81,0:04:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This show is not too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just now, was that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Praise?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.06,0:04:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she praise... us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.44,0:04:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell by the way she talks. \NShe likes the show a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.36,0:04:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla is praising us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes me happier than \Nany other good critiques.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.77,0:04:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aim for a long run! Yeah! Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.83,0:04:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to make that happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should brace ourselves for the \Nremainder of the two weeks and perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.53,0:04:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.46,0:04:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm getting motivated! Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.38,0:04:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too. Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.59,0:04:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.01,0:04:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.01,0:04:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of Kaleido Stage's future!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.48,0:05:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Death...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ending of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.65,0:05:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, please stop it with \Nthe inauspicious fortune-telling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.95,0:05:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaleido Stage is at the critical moment \Nwhether it can survive or perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.04,0:05:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So can you produce brighter futures?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there is no meaning in fortune-telling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora! It's happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.25,0:05:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh... swallowed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.34,0:05:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the time for saying \Nsomething like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People are filled with a practice room!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.26,0:05:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just said something funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.22,0:05:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why now? I didn't intend it to be funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, please come!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.97,0:05:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.66,0:05:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought everyone quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not dreaming, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.06,0:05:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe everyone decided to come back
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.69,0:05:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after they heard about \NKaleido Stage's reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.86,0:05:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I expected... It's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, this is the show \Nthat Miss Layla praised.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, the revival of Kaleido \NStage may not be a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you need to rewrite \N"Freedom" with more people, Mia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.79,0:05:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.34,0:05:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I didn't know you were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:05:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.29,0:06:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, Boss wants us to \Ngather in his room right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.17,0:06:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it means... As we thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.67,0:06:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.43,0:06:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The announcement of his decision \Nto make this a long run?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.86,0:06:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.83,0:06:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos, why don't you explain it to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will explain the situation to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.80,0:06:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.97,0:06:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos will no longer be the owner \Nof Kaleido Stage after today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:07:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, I will be the owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.35,0:07:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The current Kaleido Stage will \Nbe dissolved after today's show.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaleido Stage will be dissolved?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.28,0:07:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, we still have two weeks to perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The audience is packed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no reason to quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.75,0:07:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the show keeps on like this, \Neven a long run is a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos, don't tell me you were also dreaming \Na foolish dream like them. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.09,0:07:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A long run?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An amateur show like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.81,0:07:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will never happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.73,0:07:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, apologize to everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:46.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Get your hands off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the rest of the \Ntickets for after today,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.06,0:07:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we will refund them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.19,0:07:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave Anna alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let her go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.07,0:07:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.28,0:07:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.82,0:07:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.95,0:07:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both the Kenneth Corporation and the \NHamilton Foundation backed out as investors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.04,0:08:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Kaleido Stage is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.46,0:08:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.07,0:08:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Layla, by Mr. Hamilton's request, \NI can't make a contract with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.55,0:08:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if you wish, I don't \Nmind persuading him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.48,0:08:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I know all of your talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.93,0:08:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I definitely want you to \Njoin my Kaleido Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.64,0:08:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll welcome all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.89,0:08:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.10,0:08:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, consequently, I must also ask \Nyou to get out of the dormitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My speech is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.34,0:08:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I sold all rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.09,0:08:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you should quit, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.29,0:08:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.01,0:09:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a time for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The current Kaleido Stage \Nis practically a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.66,0:09:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just thinking that you're still \Nthere makes my blood run cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father, Kaleido Stage is not dead yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Layla, you did more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.03,0:09:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will set up the management \Noffice for you shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.45,0:09:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are many fields where you \Ncan make the most of your talents,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,either in the movies or on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.95,0:09:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, appear on the screen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.25,0:09:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard your last movie got good reviews. \NI think doing movies suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.17,0:09:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you understand how \Nmuch Kaleido Stage means to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.92,0:09:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's how you feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.33,0:09:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you want to participate in \NYuri's Kaleido Stage for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.68,0:09:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.02,0:09:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Layla, then what do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.31,0:09:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I wonder what I want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I don't want to lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.82,0:10:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to lose the partner \Nwho motivates me so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.12,0:10:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.77,0:10:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you start doing something new, you \Nwill forget about it soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.83,0:10:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, the current Kaleido Stage \Nwill not exist after tonight's show.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.88,0:10:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is something I cannot change.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.84,0:10:19.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Layla... When you look back on this later,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.43,0:10:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be glad that you \Ndid what I told you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.43,0:10:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.15,0:10:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, this evening is the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.74,0:10:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's put everything into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.41,0:10:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm afraid I'll start \Ncrying while I'm on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.37,0:10:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because this will be the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stop crying{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.09,0:11:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you think it's okay to appear in \Nthe last show feeling like you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you keep crying,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.43,0:11:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nothing will change the fact \Nthat today is the last show.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.48,0:11:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.23,0:11:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shouldn't appear on the stage \Nlike the way we feel right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.74,0:11:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since this is the last performance,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.91,0:11:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to show the audience the \Nbest performance more than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.74,0:11:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to let the audience keep the memory \Nof our Kaleido Stage in their hearts forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.04,0:11:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to do our best so we don't regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the time to be depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.03,0:11:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, you brought me to my senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's more like you, Sora.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss must feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.12,0:11:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what happened in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.15,0:11:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Kaleido Stage that he \Nbuilt up with care will be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.01,0:11:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go to see the Boss and \Ntell him how we all feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Sora.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.62,0:12:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.16,0:12:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a moment ago, we all talked backstage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.50,0:12:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone feels the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although today is our last show...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... Because it's the last show,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.01,0:12:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,let's make it the best show.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.06,0:12:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss, do you have anything you \Nwant me to tell everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.89,0:12:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one thing I want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.35,0:12:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to prepare \Nyourself for the stage like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.65,0:12:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's better not to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.49,0:12:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.74,0:12:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it is the last,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we want to do our best and \Nmake it the best show.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.75,0:13:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wanting to do our best and finish \Nit on a good note, that's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.01,0:13:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems Kaleido Stage is going \Nto end because it should end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.30,0:13:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say, Boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm disappointed in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.56,0:13:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm disappointed in you. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.98,0:13:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't understand. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.76,0:13:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What does he want me to do? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:13:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.80,0:13:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ken!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.97,0:13:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.93,0:13:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.77,0:13:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.10,0:14:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.52,0:14:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the Boss said that to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.77,0:14:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'll I do? It's our last show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.29,0:14:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I have to appear on stage \Nhalfhearted like I feel now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.12,0:14:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what Boss told you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.45,0:14:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone united because they want to do \Ntheir best since this will be the last show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.33,0:14:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.71,0:14:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you pull yourself together,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.57,0:14:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone will fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.47,0:14:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me go back to the \Ndormitory for just a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.13,0:14:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.59,0:14:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't be late for \Nthe raising of the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.34,0:14:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.85,0:14:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool! Fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.23,0:14:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.35,0:14:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen, Fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.03,0:14:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't hide. Please come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.32,0:14:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me I can't see him anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.00,0:14:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool! Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.88,0:14:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.62,0:14:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have something I want you to listen to!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.91,0:15:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't be mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand what the Boss is saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool! Please answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.08,0:15:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost the ability to see Fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.26,0:15:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, if you can see me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.27,0:15:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it means that you were chosen for the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once, there was a man who was able to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.25,0:15:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man I was talking about gradually \Nlost the ability to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.08,0:15:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lost the ability to stay at Kaleido Stage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.11,0:15:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I was told something \Nlike that by the Boss.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.04,0:15:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm not able to see Fool, either.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.13,0:15:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything is gone all at once. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.63,0:15:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't know what I should do at all.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So much has happened since the \Nfirst day I came to Kaleido Stage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.85,0:16:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But even when someone got angry \Nwith me or when I made a mistake,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.23,0:16:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I never felt like this. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.86,0:16:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm not able to see Fool {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.49,0:16:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because I can never do the legendary \Ngreat maneuver the way I am now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.74,0:16:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's not like I lost the feeling that \NI want to be as good as Miss Layla.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.47,0:16:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That hasn't changed even now, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today is the last day I can appear \Non the same stage with Miss Layla.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.47,0:16:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mia, Anna and I have been encouraging \Neach other all this time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wanted to keep doing shows \Ntogether even after this,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.97,0:16:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but our Kaleido Stage will \Nbe gone starting tomorrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.57,0:16:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought in the end I should \Nperform my best for "Freedom,"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}which we all created together. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.49,0:17:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And yet the Boss told me it'd be \Nbetter if we just didn't do it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.16,0:17:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What does he mean? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.04,0:17:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Still, I have to go. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.92,0:17:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No matter how I feel, the \Ncurtain will still be raised.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.85,0:17:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay! I'm going!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.19,0:17:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when I think that today \Nwill be the last, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.61,0:17:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.32,0:17:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.78,0:17:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.27,0:17:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's likely we won't see each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.58,0:17:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't act so tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.08,0:17:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will talk to Mr. Hamilton.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.12,0:17:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how hard you guys try,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.21,0:17:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your Kaleido Stage will be over after today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.71,0:17:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not thinking that today is the last day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.71,0:17:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look at the reality, Layla.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.05,0:18:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri, did you see our show?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Our"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.18,0:18:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the way you usually talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I don't think it's worth seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.53,0:18:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Freedom"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.36,0:18:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a story about young people \Nwho believe in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.71,0:18:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.97,0:18:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can see those lively young people \Ndoing their best for tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.12,0:18:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in spite of fighting each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.70,0:18:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The character I'm playing \Nis also that kind of person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.54,0:18:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She really believes that she can have \Nthe future that she is hoping for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.75,0:18:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The others are the same too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what kind of tough \Ncircumstances they face,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.68,0:18:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they are never overcome with \Nsorrow while they do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.93,0:18:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the characters have \Nthat kind of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.37,0:18:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I like the nature of that show.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.84,0:18:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Kaleido Stage closes its doors,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.18,0:18:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it can't close the door to my future.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.54,0:19:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will not be my last \Nshow, unless I wish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.07,0:19:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.82,0:19:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least, if I couldn't believe that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.78,0:19:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't appear on this stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.71,0:19:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is such a hackneyed, \Nidealistic point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.75,0:19:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.63,0:19:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you don't believe in your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.72,0:19:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.88,0:19:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I heard your conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.60,0:19:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, today is not the end of the show, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.23,0:19:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to make it the end \Nof the show as of today either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.28,0:19:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.66,0:19:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to appear on the stage \Nmany more times with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.91,0:19:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.24,0:19:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The curtain will be raised as scheduled.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.74,0:19:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not going to do our \Nbest because it is the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.96,0:19:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will do our best today, tomorrow, \Nand the day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.45,0:19:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we're going to put on \Nour best show all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.64,0:20:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.72,0:20:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like the audience is \Ninterested in seeing a sad show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.80,0:20:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.09,0:20:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what the Boss meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.26,0:20:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.57,0:20:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like you're finally \Nback to who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.48,0:20:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, as I thought, Miss Layla is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.06,0:20:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Maybe I don't want to lose... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.74,0:20:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't want to lose the partner \Nwho motivates me so much...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.16,0:20:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you start doing something new, you \Nwill forget about it soon enough.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.99,0:20:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is no way I can forget... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.85,0:20:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just remembering Miss Layla's words,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.71,0:20:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It will not be my last \Nshow, unless I wish it,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.84,0:20:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,makes me so emotional I could cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I messed up my makeup.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, can you go before me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.81,0:20:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Sora?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.02,0:20:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She messed up her makeup right now, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.26,0:20:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is fixing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.69,0:21:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Miss Layla.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.24,0:21:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... I'm doing my best to hurry, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.91,0:21:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will do it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.37,0:21:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.73,0:21:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Miss Layla...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.34,0:21:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk. I can't do my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I enjoyed co-starring on stage with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.06,0:21:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Miss Layla... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.69,0:21:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why would you say something like that?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is not the end, right? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.53,0:21:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.09,0:21:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it looks good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.22,0:21:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Sora.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.21,0:22:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.61,0:22:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see me again?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.09,0:22:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, unfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.51,0:22:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.60,0:22:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card represents a hope for tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.60,0:22:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hope for tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.10,0:22:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Starting tomorrow, our \Nperformance will start!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.66,0:22:36.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Kaleido Star"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.29,0:22:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't say something ridiculous! \NOf course I'm worried.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.12,0:22:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And so, since we were kicked \Nout of the dormitory,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.79,0:22:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm going to stay at Ken's house for a while.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.63,0:22:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But, Sora's worried parents \Ncame to see her, and...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.14,0:22:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's more, inside of her mother's body...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.88,0:22:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is a new life, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.39,0:22:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my father and mother's real child.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.68,0:22:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where is the place I can \Ngo back to? Where? Where?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.18,0:23:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next time on Kaleido Star, \N"Amazing Family Ties."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.14,0:23:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My wings are my dream and \Non towards the sky...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.89,0:23:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm here between the sky and the \Nroads, and facing against the wind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.54,0:23:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I'm facing forward so the sorrow \Ndoesn't rain down ever again{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.47,0:23:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I came all the way here after \NI jumped over that wall{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.39,0:23:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There are many times when \NI just want to run away{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.65,0:23:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I'm still here, so, \NI'm not daunted that much{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.07,0:23:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The poem I scribbled down, I can just \Nstart writing over from the beginning{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.45,0:24:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unable to write it well, I'm laughing{\i0}
